                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260216-102-victim733 t18260216-102-viclabel538"></join>, near Vincent-square, Westminster. The prisoner lived with us as <rs id="t18260216-102-deflabel539" type="occupation">potboy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260216-102-defend732 t18260216-102-deflabel539"></join>, for four or five months; in the evening of the 19th of January I sent him with 30s. worth of copper coin, to Mrs. Gibson's, who is a laundress; he did not return - I never saw him again until he was at Queen-square Police-office. I never got the money back.</p>
               <p>
            
